main
  h1 Pretty-print vs Compact
  p In compact mode (default) all output is on one line. Enable pretty-print via #[code Options{Pretty: true}].

  section
    h2 Compact mode
    p This card is rendered in compact mode — no newlines or indentation in the HTML source.

  section
    h2 Pretty mode
    p When #[code Pretty: true] is set the HTML source gains newlines and two-space indentation per nesting level.

  ul
    li Inline elements (#[code a], #[code span], #[code strong], etc.) stay on one line even in pretty mode.
    li Void elements (#[code br], #[code hr], #[code input]) never get a closing tag.
    li The doctype line always gets its own line in pretty mode.

footer
  p Pretty-print affects HTML source readability only — rendered output is identical.
